    <summary>04/26/1993: In San Jose, five gunmen stormed the Costa Rican Supreme Court and seized nineteen Supreme Court justices, along with five other hostages. The gunmen demanded $20 million in ransom, safe passage to a country with no extradition, and the release of three men from prison. The incident ended on four days later when the gunmen released the hostages in exchange for $150,000 and a promise of safe passage to Panama or Guatemala. The gunmen were arrested at the airport.</summary>
